OL,4,Cpilgrimage so legacy lives on
OL,6,FJoe Withnall's son, Ray, is amongst
OL,7,Fthose paying respects and said: "Every
OL,8,Fmoment I get, I tell people that he
OL,9,Fwas a Normandy veteran and of course
OL,10,Fhe was awarded the Legion D'Honneur
OL,11,Fwhich is a great honour."
OL,13,FJohn McHugh's mother was heavily
OL,14,Fpregnant with him when her husband
OL,15,Fdied from his wounds the day after D-
OL,16,FDay.
OL,18,F"I'm so proud it hurts," he said today.
OL,20,FITV Granada's Paul Crone reports from
OL,21,FSword Beach, Normandy.
