OL,6,FA shock awaited the naval teenager as
OL,7,Fdawn broke and he viewed the ensuing
OL,8,Fcarnage and chaos.
OL,10,F"All the bodies were in the water, a
OL,11,Flot of them," he said.
OL,13,F"The vessels had been sunk. There were
OL,14,Fdestroyers, cruisers, battleships and
OL,15,Faircraft carriers. They were all
OL,16,Ffiring over the top of us and firing
OL,17,Fright into France, as far as Caen."
OL,19,FAfter a German plane was shot down,
OL,20,Fthe Crane's crew were sent to pick the
OL,21,Fpilot up from the Channel.
